cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically state-dependent channels with side information at the transmitter and the problem of maximizing transmission rate under certain constraints. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses communication systems and signal transmission, which suggests the sub-categories cs.COMM (Communication) and cs.SI (Signal Processing). The use of i.i.d. sequences and the consideration of discrete interference suggest the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
